title: (x) Fitnessphere logo - Corvinus/Skyline/Quirinus {Tiff, Stephen}
content:
Can someone help me ID this font? It's similar to the old PInnacle Fitness logotype (now extinct, so I couldn't locate a photo). Something similar will do. I looked at Altered Ego's "Chevron" but the weight is too light...

Thanks in advance.

 ![](http://web.archive.org/web/20150415222354im_/http:/typophile.com/files/sample_4996.jpg)
author: cchs

comments.content: Might not be an exact match: [http://www.myfonts.com/fonts/dsgnhaus/apcorvinus-skyline/](http://web.archive.org/web/20150415222354/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/dsgnhaus/apcorvinus-skyline/ "http://www.myfonts.com/fonts/dsgnhaus/apcorvinus-skyline/")

Could be The Font Bureau's [Skyline](http://web.archive.org/web/20150415222354/http:/www.fontshop.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=catalog.fontdetail&displayfontid=FB.2884.0.1&attributes.sampleSize=48&sampleText=FITNESSPHERE&sampleSize=84).  
Alternatively, [Quirinus Bold](http://web.archive.org/web/20150415222354/http:/www.fontshop.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=catalog.fontdetail&displayfontid=C.106320.0.0&attributes.sampleSize=48&sampleText=FITNESSPHERE&sampleSize=48).
